actuator.channels.description: ID of the multiple channels of the actuator: Beam boxes for NBI, EC or IC launcher, ... {static}

actuator.code.description: Generic decription of the code specific parameters for the code that has produced this IDS

actuator.code.output_flag.description: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used. {dynamic}

actuator.code.parameters.description: List of the code specific parameters in XML format {constant}

actuator.generic_dynamic.description: Generic 2D dynamic slot for storing an actuator control parameter (e.g. the angle of an ECRH mirror) {dynamic} [mixed]

actuator.generic_dynamic_error_index.description: Index in the error_description list for "generic_dynamic" {constant}

actuator.ids_properties.description: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

actuator.ids_properties.comment.description: Any comment describing the content of this IDS {constant}

actuator.ids_properties.homogeneous_time.description: 1 if the time of this IDS is homogeneous. In this case, the time values for this IDS are stored in ../time just below the root of this IDS. Otherwise, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree. {constant}

actuator.name.description: Name of the actuator (IC, EC, NBI, LH) {static} [-]

actuator.power.description: Power delivered at the output of the actuator, in the vessel (NB this is before the coupling / beam blocking / shine through / orbit losses calculations) {dynamic} [W]

actuator.power_error_index.description: Index in the error_description list for "power" {constant}
